Pattern 1: Fixed-Size Sliding Window
The window width remains constant. You maintain a running state by adding the incoming element on the right and dropping the outgoing element on the left.

1. Easy: Maximum Average Subarray I (LeetCode 643)
The Concept: Find a contiguous subarray of a fixed length k that has the maximum average value.

The Shortcut: Calculate the sum of the first k elements. Then slide the window across the array: add nums[i] and subtract nums[i - k]. Track the maximum sum found, then divide by k at the very end to avoid floating-point errors during the loop.

Code:
class Solution {
    public double findMaxAverage(int[] nums, int k) {
        int sum=0;
        double max=Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        int n=nums.length;
        int j=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            sum+=nums[i];

            if(sum>max&&i-j+1==k){
                    max=sum;
            } 

            while(i-j+1>=k){
                    sum=sum-nums[j];
                j++;
            }
        }
        return (double)max/k;
    }
}
